                              - March 2, 2019
                           Thank you for your post. Is it possible we
                           engage in too much speculation and ‚Äúoverthink‚Äù
                           regarding the concept of climate change? The
                           climate will change‚Ä¶with or without humans.
                           What‚Äôs our plan of action when a volcano erupts
                           and spews ash into the atmosphere? How will we
                           protect the environment and minimize impact on
                           climate? Multiple volcanoes? A subsequent giant
                           meteor that impacts the planet? I‚Äôm tired of
                           thinking in terms of gloom and doom and
                           speculation of what ‚Äúmight‚Äù happen. Could we
                           have prevented the last ice age as human
                           beings? Everyone thinks they are experts and
                           have crystal balls into the planet‚Äôs future.
                           We‚Äôre ants. We imagine we have more control
                           over some outcome that‚Äôs not certain in any
                           way. There‚Äôs freedom in ignorance! Where did
                           our world view come from? Mad Max and
