                 I conjecture all this because you‚Äôve bought the bill of
                 goods on ‚Äúorganizing principles.‚Äù I know, it sounds nice
                 and fair, and it would all work fine with good-natured
                 people like you dealing with minor matters, where little
                 is at stake for anyone involved. In such cases,
                 scientific-sounding abstractions like ‚Äúhyper-aggression‚Äù
                 and ‚Äúcompetitive‚Äù and ‚Äúcooperative‚Äù spaces seem as
                 obvious as the blue sky. You can easily fill in the
                 definitions and assume that others have exactly the same
                 ideas in mind, no need for Robert‚Äôs rules of order.
                 But a few weeks after joining a community association
                 based on the ‚Äúcooperative organizing principle,‚Äù you
                 start fretting to me about how you keep getting shut down
                 for your ‚Äúcompetitiveness‚Äù and your ‚Äúlack of empathy for
                 other perspectives,‚Äù even though all you did was raise a
